## 4. Training Data

> What data was used to build or train this model? How was it collected? What
> populations, geographies, languages, and time periods does it cover? What
> is missing?

The data used to train the model comes from multiple sources 1) Water quality testing reports provided by bottled water brands to the FDA and available freely on the FDA website, 2) EPA water quality reports by municipality, publicly available from the EPA website, 3) Lab testin data purchased from Certified laboratories, a third-party food and beverage testing laboratory, as well as 4) climate data available from the National Weather Service website and geospatial data avalable from USGS website. All data is only for bottled and packaged water sold in the United States for consumers in the United States, and provided only in English. Data is generally not current, FDA data is 12-18 months behind and EPA data is only repported once a year. Combined that data covers only 60% of available brands found in supermarket chains. Most of the missing datais from store-brand or regional brands. The most current version of the data was used for training, Spring 2025 reports.   

