## 5. Evaluation Data & Metrics

> How was performance measured? What metrics were used — accuracy, sensitivity,
> specificity, F1, AUC, RMSE? On what test set? Is it independent from the
> training data?

Performance was primarity measured using the F1 score which will treat each level (letter grade) equally, ensure classification accuracy, to ensure precision and recall. Cohen's Kappa was also used to measure how the model performs over random guessing. Since the model is intended to provide health safety information, sensitivity and specificity tests were conducted to ensure unsafe water is accurately predicted and unsafe waster is not lables as safe. The data set used for this purpose was older vresoins of the FDA water quality result, EPAmunicipal water quality reports, and older water testing reports from independent labs.This wat the same sources of data are usd, but the data used is different than the training data.   

